QQQ</a>) <font color=\"green\">+1.1%</font>, Dow (<a href='https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/dia' title='SPDR Dow Jones Industrial Average ETF'>DIA</a>) <font color=\"green\">+0.85%</font>.<div class=\"tiny-share-widget\" data-id=\"1120852\" data-linked=\"U.S. stock futures are enjoying a nice Independence Day rally along with equity markets across...\" data-tweet=\"$SPY $QQQ $DIA - U.S. stock futures are enjoying a nice Independence Day rally along with equity markets across the globe, boosted by Portugal&#39;s government doing its best to stay alive and the ousting of Mohamed Morsi in Egypt. S&amp;P (SPY) +0.6%, Nasdaq (... https://seekingalpha.com/news/1120852?source=tweet\" data-url=\"https://seekingalpha.com/news/1120852\"><div class=\"icon share-btn c-email\" title=\"Email a friend\">&nbsp;</div><div class=\"icon share-btn c-twitter\" title=\"Share on Twitter\">&nbsp;</div><div class=\"icon share-btn c-facebook\" title=\"Share on Facebook\">&nbsp;</div><div class=\"icon share-btn c-linkedin\" title=\"Share on Linkedin\">&nbsp;</div></div><span class=\"mc_gray_separator\">|</span>  8:30 AM <span class='mc_gray_separator'>|</span> <span class='comments-n'><span class='comments-container '>4&nbsp;<span class='comments-number'>Comments</span></span></span></div></div></li><li class=\"n-box-item sa-box-item\" data-id=\"1120842\" data-ts=\"1372940357\"><div class=\"media media-overflow-fix\"><div class=\"media-left\"><a class=\"box-ticker\" href=\"/symbol/FXB\" target=\"_blank\">FXB</a></div><div class=\"media-body\"><h4 class=\"media-heading\"><a href=\"/news/1120842\" sasource=\"on_the_move_news_fidelity\" target=\"_blank\">The minutes of today&#39;s BOE&#39;s policy meeting, due for release on July 17, may attract extra...</a></h4><p>The minutes of today's BOE's policy meeting, due for release on July 17, may attract extra interest given that this was Mark Carney's first one as governor. The suspicion is that the bank has been waiting for him to arrive before easing further. The BOE's <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/currents/search?query=boe\" target=\"_blank\">dovish statement</a> appears to designed to assure that no rate hikes are coming in the near future, and, if anything, the next move could be more loosening. Sterling (NYSEARCA:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/FXB\" title=\"Invesco CurrencyShares British Pound Sterling Trust ETF\">FXB</a>) <font color=\"red\">-1.2%</font> at $1.5102, and stabilizes a bit after dropping sharply following the statement.</p><div class=\"tiny-share-widget\" data-id=\"1120842\" data-linked=\"The minutes of today&#39;s BOE&#39;s policy meeting, due for release on July 17, may attract extra...\" data-tweet=\"$FXB $FKU $EWU - The minutes of today&#39;s BOE&#39;s policy meeting, due for release on July 17, may attract extra interest given that this was Mark Carney&#39;s first one as governor. The suspicion is that the bank has been waiting for him to arrive before easing... https://seekingalpha.com/news/1120842?source=tweet\" data-url=\"https://seekingalpha.com/news/1120842\"><div class=\"icon share-btn c-email\" title=\"Email a friend\">&nbsp;</div><div class=\"icon share-btn c-twitter\" title=\"Share on Twitter\">&nbsp;</div><div class=\"icon share-btn c-facebook\" title=\"Share on Facebook\">&nbsp;</div><div class=\"icon share-btn c-linkedin\" title=\"Share on Linkedin\">&nbsp;</div></div><span class=\"mc_gray_separator\">|</span>  8:19 AM </div></div></li><li class=\"n-box-item sa-box-item\" data-id=\"1120802\" data-ts=\"1372936950\"><div class=\"media media-overflow-fix\"><div class=\"media-left\"><a class=\"box-ticker\" href=\"/symbol/FXB\" target=\"_blank\">FXB</a></div><div class=\"media-body\"><h4 class=\"media-heading\"><a href=\"/news/1120802\" sasource=\"on_the_move_news_fidelity\" target=\"_blank\">Sterling (NYSEARCA:FXB) drops like a stone following the BOE&#39;s dovish statement after its...</a></h4>Sterling (NYSEARCA:<a href='https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/FXB' title='Invesco CurrencyShares British Pound Sterling Trust ETF'>FXB</a>) drops like a stone following the BOE's dovish statement after its decision to <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/currents/search?query=boe\">leave things</a> as they are and is now <font color=\"red\">-1.3%</font> at $1.5088. The FTSE jumps a bit and is <font color=\"green\">+1.8%</font>.<div class=\"tiny-share-widget\" data-id=\"1120802\" data-linked=\"Sterling (NYSEARCA:FXB) drops like a stone following the BOE&#39;s dovish statement after its...\" data-tweet=\"$FXB $FKU $EWU - Sterling (NYSEARCA:FXB) drops like a stone following the BOE&#39;s dovish statement after its decision to leave things as they are and is now -1.3% at $1.5088. The FTSE jumps a bit and is +1.8%. https://seekingalpha.com/news/1120802?source=tweet\" data-url=\"https://seekingalpha.com/news/1120802\"><div class=\"icon share-btn c-email\" title=\"Email a friend\">&nbsp;</div><div class=\"icon share-btn c-twitter\" title=\"Share on Twitter\">&nbsp;</div><div class=\"icon share-btn c-facebook\" title=\"Share on Facebook\">&nbsp;</div><div class=\"icon share-btn c-linkedin\" title=\"Share on Linkedin\">&nbsp;</div></div><span class=\"mc_gray_separator\">|</span>  7:22 AM </div></div></li><li class=\"n-box-item sa-box-item\" data-id=\"1120722\" data-ts=\"1372931400\"><div class=\"media media-overflow-fix\"><div class=\"media-left\"><a class=\"box-ticker\" href=\"/symbol/\" target=\"_blank\"></a></div><div class=\"media-body\"><h4 class=\"media-heading\"><a href=\"/news/1120722\" sasource=\"on_the_move_news_fidelity\" target=\"_blank\">Egypt&#39;s CASE30 Index soars 7.4% following the army&#39;s removal of President Mohamed Morsi last...</a></h4><p>Egypt's CASE30 Index <font color=\"green\">soars 7.4%</font> following the army's removal of President Mohamed Morsi last night and the suspension of Egypt's constitution in what <a href=\"http://www.theglobeandmail.com/news/world/was-morsis-ouster-a-coup-detat-or-not/article12974954/\" target=\"_blank\">may or may not</a> have been a coup d'etat, depending on how delicate you need to be with the use of language. The large rise <a href=\"http://blogs.ft.com/beyond-brics/2013/07/04/egyptian-shares-surge-on-opening/#axzz2Y4HQfWB1\" target=\"_blank\">forced a halt</a> in trading, as it exceeded the Egyptian Exchange's 5% limit on daily movement in the index. Meanwhile, crude oil is <font color=\"red\">-0.3%</font> at $100.90.</p><div class=\"tiny-share-widget\" data-id=\"1120722\" data-linked=\"Egypt&#39;s CASE30 Index soars 7.4% following the army&#39;s removal of President Mohamed Morsi last...\" data-tweet=\"$EGPT - Egypt&#39;s CASE30 Index soars 7.4% following the army&#39;s removal of President Mohamed Morsi last night and the suspension of Egypt&#39;s constitution in what may or may not have been a coup d&#39;etat, depending on how delicate you need to be with the use o... https://seekingalpha.com/news/1120722?source=tweet\" data-url=\"https://seekingalpha.com/news/1120722\"><div class=\"icon share-btn c-email\" title=\"Email a friend\">&nbsp;</div><div class=\"icon share-btn c-twitter\" title=\"Share on Twitter\">&nbsp;</div><div class=\"icon share-btn c-facebook\" title=\"Share on Facebook\">&nbsp;</div><div class=\"icon share-btn c-linkedin\" title=\"Share on Linkedin\">&nbsp;</div></div><span class=\"mc_gray_separator\">|</span>  5:50 AM </div></div></li><li class=\"n-box-item sa-box-item\" data-id=\"1120712\" data-ts=\"1372930242\"><div class=\"media media-overflow-fix\"><div class=\"media-left\"><a class=\"box-ticker\" href=\"/symbol/FEZ\" target=\"_blank\">FEZ</a></div><div class=\"media-body\"><h4 class=\"media-heading\"><a href=\"/news/1120712\" sasource=\"on_the_move_news_fidelity\" target=\"_blank\">European shares (NYSEARCA:FEZ) are higher as Portugal&#39;s leaders work to preserve the governing...</a></h4><a href=\"http://www.reuters.com/article/2013/07/04/us-markets-global-idUSBRE88901C20130704\" target=\"_blank\">European shares</a> (NYSEARCA:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/FEZ\" title=\"SPDR EURO STOXX 50 ETF\">FEZ</a>) are higher as Portugal's leaders <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/currents/post/1120702\" target=\"_blank\">work to preserve</a> the governing coalition, and ahead of monetary policy  decisions by the BOE and the ECB later, as well as the U.S. jobs report tomorrow. Economists don't expect either of the central banks to change their policies, although there's hope in the market that Mario Draghi will come out with some soothing words after recent turmoil. EU Stoxx 50 <font color=\"green\">+0.7%</font>, London <font color=\"green\">+0.9%</font>, Paris <font color=\"green\">+0.8%</font>, Frankfurt <font color=\"green\">+0.6%</font>, Madrid <font color=\"green\">+0.7%</font>, Milan <font color=\"green\">+0.45%</font>.<div class=\"tiny-share-widget\" data-id=\"1120712\" data-linked=\"European shares (NYSEARCA:FEZ) are higher as Portugal&#39;s leaders work to preserve the governing...\" data-tweet=\"$FEZ - European shares (NYSEARCA:FEZ) are higher as Portugal&#39;s leaders work to preserve the governing coalition, and ahead of monetary policy decisions by the BOE and the ECB later, as well as the U.S. jobs report tomorrow. Economists don&#39;t expect eithe... https://seekingalpha.com/news/1120712?source=tweet\" data-url=\"https://seekingalpha.com/news/1120712\"><div class=\"icon share-btn c-email\" title=\"Email a friend\">&nbsp;</div><div class=\"icon share-btn c-twitter\" title=\"Share on Twitter\">&nbsp;</div><div class=\"icon share-btn c-facebook\" title=\"Share on Facebook\">&nbsp;</div><div class=\"icon share-btn c-linkedin\" title=\"Share on Linkedin\">&nbsp;</div></div><span class=\"mc_gray_separator\">|</span>  5:30 AM </div></div></li><li class=\"n-box-item sa-box-item\" data-id=\"1120702\" data-ts=\"1372929699\"><div class=\"media media-overflow-fix\"><div class=\"media-left\"><a class=\"box-ticker\" href=\"/symbol/\" target=\"_blank\"></a></div><div class=\"media-body\"><h4 class=\"media-heading\"><a href=\"/news/1120702\" sasource=\"on_the_move_news_fidelity\" target=\"_blank\">Portuguese Prime Minister Pedro Passos Coelho held what was reported to be &quot;a very constructive&quot;...</a></h4><p>Portuguese Prime Minister Pedro Passos Coelho held what was reported to be \"<a href=\"http://online.wsj.com/article/SB10001424127887323899704578582931660976470.html\" target=\"_blank\">a very constructive</a>\" meeting yesterday with Paulo Portas, the head of junior coalition party, the Democratic &amp; Social Center Party, who resigned on Tuesday as foreign minister amid frustration with austerity. The two were due to meet again today as they work to preserve the government. The positive signals have been enough to allow Portuguese stocks and bonds to recover from the drubbing they took yesterday due to the political turmoil. The PSI 20 is <font color=\"green\">+2.5%</font>, while 10-year government bond yields have fallen back towards 7% after topping 8%.</p><div class=\"tiny-share-widget\" data-id=\"1120702\" data-linked=\"Portuguese Prime Minister Pedro Passos Coelho held what was reported to be &quot;a very constructive&quot;...\" data-tweet=\"Portuguese Prime Minister Pedro Passos Coelho held what was reported to be &quot;a very constructive&quot; meeting yesterday with Paulo Portas, the head of junior coalition party, the Democratic &amp; Social Center Party, who resigned on Tuesday as foreign minister a... https://seekingalpha.com/news/1120702?source=tweet\" data-url=\"https://seekingalpha.com/news/1120702\"><div class=\"icon share-btn c-email\" title=\"Email a friend\">&nbsp;</div><div class=\"icon share-btn c-twitter\" title=\"Share on Twitter\">&nbsp;</div><div class=\"icon share-btn c-facebook\" title=\"Share on Facebook\">&nbsp;</div><div class=\"icon share-btn c-linkedin\" title=\"Share on Linkedin\">&nbsp;</div></div><span class=\"mc_gray_separator\">|</span>  5:21 AM </div></div></li><li cl